<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <title>Students</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/style.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1>Students</h1>
        <p class="long-text">Keep pushing forward, dear students, for every challenge you face today is molding you into 
            the resilient, capable individual you're destined to become. Embrace each stumble as a stepping
             stone, each setback as a setup for a remarkable comeback. Your journey is not defined by the obstacles
              you encounter but by the strength and perseverance you exhibit in overcoming them. Believe in your abilities,
               stay focused on your goals, and let your passion fuel your drive towards success. Remember, greatness lies
                within you, waiting to be unleashed through dedication and hard work. So, rise above the doubts, defy the odds,
                 and let your determination illuminate the path to your dreams. You've got this!
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="body-content">
        <ul class="students">
            <% students.forEach(function(student) { %>
                <li><%= student.name %> | <%= student.school %></li>
            <% }) %>
        </ul>
        
    </div>
    <button id="test">Click me</button>

    <script type="text/javascript">
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function (event) {
            // Select the test button using querySelector
            var testButton = document.querySelector('#test');
            
            // Add an event listener to the button for the click event
            testButton.addEventListener('click', function() {
                // Add alert("CLICKED!") in the listener
                alert("CLICKED!");
            });
        });
    </script>
    
    <script type="text/javascript">
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function (event) {
            // Create a link element
            var createStudentLink = document.createElement('a');
            
            // Set the href attribute to /students/create
            createStudentLink.href = '/students/create';
            
            // Set the text content of the link
            createStudentLink.textContent = 'Create New Student';
            
            // Append the link to a suitable parent element in the DOM, such as the body
            document.body.appendChild(createStudentLink);
        });
    </script>


</body>





</html>
